      "originalText": "DIAGRAM SPEC — CALM CLI Command Taxonomy (Chapter 3.1)\n\nLayout: Tree diagram, top-to-bottom orientation.\n\nROOT NODE (top, centred):\n  Box labelled: `calm` (or `npx @finos/calm-cli`)\n  Caption: 'v1.45.0'\n\n8 PRIMARY COMMAND BRANCHES below the root node:\n  validate | generate | diff | timeline | docify | template | init-ai | hub\n\nEach primary command box has 2-4 KEY FLAG child nodes beneath it:\n\n  validate branch:\n    Flags: `-a <arch>`, `-p <pattern>`, `-f junit`, `--strict`\n    Note annotation: 'schema-only vs pattern conformance'\n\n  generate branch:\n    Flags: `-p <pattern>`, `-o <file>`, `--option-choices`\n\n  diff branch:\n    Flags: `-a`, `-b`, `-f summary`, `--exit-code`\n    Note annotation: 'exit-code = gate on unexpected changes'\n\n  timeline branch:\n    Flags: `-a <files...>`, `-o <file>`\n\n  docify branch:\n    No sub-flags shown; brief label 'generates doc site'\n\n  template branch:\n    No sub-flags shown; brief label 'Handlebars output'\n\n  init-ai branch:\n    Flags: `-p copilot|kiro|claude|codex`, `-d <path>`\n\n  hub branch (EXPANDS FURTHER — it is a subcommand group):\n    Three sub-branches under hub:\n      push → (architecture / pattern / standard / control-requirement)\n      pull → (architecture / pattern / standard)\n      list → (architectures / namespaces / patterns / standards)\n\nTitle above diagram: 'The CALM CLI command taxonomy'\n\nStyle: B&W only. No colour. Clean tree structure with thin connector lines.\nAll boxes use rounded-corner rectangles. Hub branch should be visually wider\nto accommodate its sub-branches. Root node has heavier border to draw the eye."
